author: COMSOL
description:
This is an example of a model of an induction motor in which the eddy currents are induced in the rotor by the time harmonic currents on the stator windings and the rotation of the rotor. The air gap between the rotor and stator is assumed asymmetric and the resulting vibrations in the motor are analyzed.

In this example, electromagnetic simulation of an induction motor in performed in 2D whereas the multibody dynamics simulation in performed in 3D. The rotational torque, when an alternating current is passed through the stator windings, are calculated as a function of time is used in multibody dynamics in order to compute the rotor speed accounting for inertial effects.
